Resource Profile: CGM Data Submission Bundle

Official URL: http://argo.run/cgm/StructureDefinition/cgm-data-submission-bundle Version: 0.1.0
Draft as of 2024-05-06 Computable Name: CGMDataSubmissionBundle

Once a Data Submitter is connected to the EHR, it can write data by submitting a batch Bundle to the EHR FHIR sever’s / submission endpoint. The submission bundle includes a Bundle.meta.tag value of cgm-data-submission-bundle to support ingestion workflows on servers with limited data ingestion capabilities. The tag has no impact on the meaning of the bundle, and can safely be ignored by servers that offer a general-purpose POST / endpoint.

The Bundle entry array includes any combination of

  • CGM Summary PDF Reports (Profile, Example)
  • CGM Summary Observation (Profile, Example)
    • Mean Glucose (Profile, Example)
    • Times in Ranges (Profile, Example)
    • Glucose Management Index (Profile, Example)
    • Coefficient of Variations (Profile, Example)
    • Sensor Days of Wear (Profile, Example)
    • Sensor Active Percentage (Profile, Example)
  • CGM Devices (Profile, Example)
  • CGM Sensor Readings (Profile, Example)

Usage:

  • This Resource Profile is not used by any profiles in this Implementation Guide

Constraints

IdGradePath(s)DetailsRequirements
bdl-1errorBundletotal only when a search or history
: total.empty() or (type = 'searchset') or (type = 'history')
bdl-2errorBundleentry.search only when a search
: entry.search.empty() or (type = 'searchset')
bdl-3errorBundleentry.request mandatory for batch/transaction/history, otherwise prohibited
: entry.all(request.exists() = (%resource.type = 'batch' or %resource.type = 'transaction' or %resource.type = 'history'))
bdl-4errorBundleentry.response mandatory for batch-response/transaction-response/history, otherwise prohibited
: entry.all(response.exists() = (%resource.type = 'batch-response' or %resource.type = 'transaction-response' or %resource.type = 'history'))
bdl-5errorBundle.entry, Bundle.entry:patient, Bundle.entry:observation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummary, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMolar, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryTimesInRanges, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryGMI, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryCoefficientOfVariation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryDaysOfWear, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummarySensorActivePercentage, Bundle.entry:observation/device, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMolar, Bundle.entry:diagnosticReport, Bundle.entry:devicemust be a resource unless there's a request or response
: resource.exists() or request.exists() or response.exists()
bdl-7errorBundleFullUrl must be unique in a bundle, or else entries with the same fullUrl must have different meta.versionId (except in history bundles)
: (type = 'history') or entry.where(fullUrl.exists()).select(fullUrl&resource.meta.versionId).isDistinct()
bdl-8errorBundle.entry, Bundle.entry:patient, Bundle.entry:observation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummary, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMolar, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryTimesInRanges, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryGMI, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryCoefficientOfVariation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryDaysOfWear, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummarySensorActivePercentage, Bundle.entry:observation/device, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMolar, Bundle.entry:diagnosticReport, Bundle.entry:devicefullUrl cannot be a version specific reference
: fullUrl.contains('/_history/').not()
bdl-9errorBundleA document must have an identifier with a system and a value
: type = 'document' implies (identifier.system.exists() and identifier.value.exists())
bdl-10errorBundleA document must have a date
: type = 'document' implies (timestamp.hasValue())
bdl-11errorBundleA document must have a Composition as the first resource
: type = 'document' implies entry.first().resource.is(Composition)
bdl-12errorBundleA message must have a MessageHeader as the first resource
: type = 'message' implies entry.first().resource.is(MessageHeader)
ele-1error**ALL** elementsAll FHIR elements must have a @value or children
: hasValue() or (children().count() > id.count())
ext-1error**ALL** extensionsMust have either extensions or value[x], not both
: extension.exists() != value.exists()

IdGradePath(s)DetailsRequirements
bdl-1errorBundletotal only when a search or history
: total.empty() or (type = 'searchset') or (type = 'history')
bdl-2errorBundleentry.search only when a search
: entry.search.empty() or (type = 'searchset')
bdl-3errorBundleentry.request mandatory for batch/transaction/history, otherwise prohibited
: entry.all(request.exists() = (%resource.type = 'batch' or %resource.type = 'transaction' or %resource.type = 'history'))
bdl-4errorBundleentry.response mandatory for batch-response/transaction-response/history, otherwise prohibited
: entry.all(response.exists() = (%resource.type = 'batch-response' or %resource.type = 'transaction-response' or %resource.type = 'history'))
bdl-5errorBundle.entry, Bundle.entry:patient, Bundle.entry:observation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummary, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMolar, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryTimesInRanges, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryGMI, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryCoefficientOfVariation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryDaysOfWear, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummarySensorActivePercentage, Bundle.entry:observation/device, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMolar, Bundle.entry:diagnosticReport, Bundle.entry:devicemust be a resource unless there's a request or response
: resource.exists() or request.exists() or response.exists()
bdl-7errorBundleFullUrl must be unique in a bundle, or else entries with the same fullUrl must have different meta.versionId (except in history bundles)
: (type = 'history') or entry.where(fullUrl.exists()).select(fullUrl&resource.meta.versionId).isDistinct()
bdl-8errorBundle.entry, Bundle.entry:patient, Bundle.entry:observation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummary, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMolar, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryTimesInRanges, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryGMI, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryCoefficientOfVariation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryDaysOfWear, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummarySensorActivePercentage, Bundle.entry:observation/device, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMolar, Bundle.entry:diagnosticReport, Bundle.entry:devicefullUrl cannot be a version specific reference
: fullUrl.contains('/_history/').not()
bdl-9errorBundleA document must have an identifier with a system and a value
: type = 'document' implies (identifier.system.exists() and identifier.value.exists())
bdl-10errorBundleA document must have a date
: type = 'document' implies (timestamp.hasValue())
bdl-11errorBundleA document must have a Composition as the first resource
: type = 'document' implies entry.first().resource.is(Composition)
bdl-12errorBundleA message must have a MessageHeader as the first resource
: type = 'message' implies entry.first().resource.is(MessageHeader)
ele-1error**ALL** elementsAll FHIR elements must have a @value or children
: hasValue() or (children().count() > id.count())
ext-1error**ALL** extensionsMust have either extensions or value[x], not both
: extension.exists() != value.exists()

bdl-1errorBundletotal only when a search or history
: total.empty() or (type = 'searchset') or (type = 'history')
bdl-2errorBundleentry.search only when a search
: entry.search.empty() or (type = 'searchset')
bdl-3errorBundleentry.request mandatory for batch/transaction/history, otherwise prohibited
: entry.all(request.exists() = (%resource.type = 'batch' or %resource.type = 'transaction' or %resource.type = 'history'))
bdl-4errorBundleentry.response mandatory for batch-response/transaction-response/history, otherwise prohibited
: entry.all(response.exists() = (%resource.type = 'batch-response' or %resource.type = 'transaction-response' or %resource.type = 'history'))
bdl-5errorBundle.entry, Bundle.entry:patient, Bundle.entry:observation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummary, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMolar, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryTimesInRanges, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryGMI, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryCoefficientOfVariation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryDaysOfWear, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummarySensorActivePercentage, Bundle.entry:observation/device, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMolar, Bundle.entry:diagnosticReport, Bundle.entry:devicemust be a resource unless there's a request or response
: resource.exists() or request.exists() or response.exists()
bdl-7errorBundleFullUrl must be unique in a bundle, or else entries with the same fullUrl must have different meta.versionId (except in history bundles)
: (type = 'history') or entry.where(fullUrl.exists()).select(fullUrl&resource.meta.versionId).isDistinct()
bdl-8errorBundle.entry, Bundle.entry:patient, Bundle.entry:observation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummary, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryMeanGlucoseMolar, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryTimesInRanges, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryGMI, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryCoefficientOfVariation, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummaryDaysOfWear, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSummarySensorActivePercentage, Bundle.entry:observation/device, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMass, Bundle.entry:observation/cgmSensorReadingMolar, Bundle.entry:diagnosticReport, Bundle.entry:devicefullUrl cannot be a version specific reference
: fullUrl.contains('/_history/').not()
bdl-9errorBundleA document must have an identifier with a system and a value
: type = 'document' implies (identifier.system.exists() and identifier.value.exists())
bdl-10errorBundleA document must have a date
: type = 'document' implies (timestamp.hasValue())
bdl-11errorBundleA document must have a Composition as the first resource
: type = 'document' implies entry.first().resource.is(Composition)
bdl-12errorBundleA message must have a MessageHeader as the first resource
: type = 'message' implies entry.first().resource.is(MessageHeader)
ele-1error**ALL** elementsAll FHIR elements must have a @value or children
: hasValue() or (children().count() > id.count())
ext-1error**ALL** extensionsMust have either extensions or value[x], not both
: extension.exists() != value.exists()
